column5: You are very good at cleaning up after yourselves as we did the same cabin for 6 years the following week! Great place, though we did not get to meet the new owners who took over the year after we quit going. We had some great days fishing off Devils' Point there. My brother and I would love to take you up on that, but the week you go won't allow it. We got to Pakwash now 2 weeks later.
Thanks, we have ours two new member from home base.

We have 6 going this, need 2 more to keep the big log cabin.....$390.00 if you bring own boat/cabin or $500.00 for their boat/cabin.....Tallpine camp on Wabaskang lake.....will be 18 years going there...I will bring all the foods, $80-100.00 per person...May 24-31...if you more info call me 920-667-4243 after 7:30 pm. or e-mail.
Good luck filling a hole on the internet. I did it one time with one guy and it was a monumental blunder on my part. Lots of good luck to you.

Two sides to every story. I have used WC to fill trips and have had great luck getting quality people. In fact one of the guys I got off of WC turned out to be one of my best friends and we fished together on at least 10 trips. Good Luck, Mike Kansas
Try and get together to discuss the trip or at least several phone calls to make sure everybody knows the ground rules. I could easily see a disaster on the horizon, or a fishin buddy for life.
Thanks, will be checking them out ...we had some dandy one in the past so we will talk first or like the saying "show me the money baby".....we are all from Wisconsin....

Well, if you're all from WI then you can't go wrong. :-) I'd recommend a personal meeting with whoever you choose, just to get a better picture. One last thing I'd recommend is to check them out on CCAP. In WI almost all municipal code violations, criminal and civil activities in the state are recorded there. Nice to know if you're going with an ax murderer, or somebody with a DUI history that could mess you up at the border.

>Good luck filling a hole on the internet. I did it one time >with one guy and it was a monumental blunder on my part. > >Lots of good luck to you. That must make for some fun stories now that its behind you goldeneagle. I can just imagine being at camp for a week with some moron that everyone wants to kill and you invited him!! LOL
I dont see what the trouble would be at the border, the guy would just have to unload his stuff and figure out himself how to get home! your problem is not my problem.
>Good luck filling a hole on the internet. I did it one time >with one guy and it was a monumental blunder on my part. > >Lots of good luck to you. Excuse me At least your batting .500 :popcorn:
